task.summary: I got rid of the individual note items and added a ListView widget. I also added an array of Strings to act as place holder notes.
Updated the id of ListView to @android:id/list. Got rid of runtime error on app launch.

Added Edit Activity Got rid of String Array of dummy notes Added ArrayList for notes Added functionality to add strings to ArrayList notes with enter button Added long press that retrieves note from ArrayList and displays note as a toast
Needed: edit_activity launch with pressed note Edit selected string in array with edit activity Ability to delete notes

Changed the onClick listener for enter button so it is added in the XML and not in onCreate method in order to make the code seem less hacked together.
It now calls addItem function in MainAcitivity. Also made the enter text box clear to an empty string after note is added.

Added a save to file functionality. Notes should persist now.
Still need to implement the dave edit and delete feature. Which might require changing the way long press passes Intent.

Added a save to file functionality. Notes should persist now.
Still need to implement the dave edit and delete feature. Which might require changing the way long press passes Intent.
Added onPause to edit acitiviy. It does nothing besides call super.onPause. Got rid of new File creation and if exists in main activity for the onPause activity. Just a try catch now.
Added edit and delete functionality in EditActivity. Appropriate changes made to support this in the PopulateArray() method of MainActivity. Confirmed functionality through testing.
Made a change to correct a small potential error I introduced in MainActivity. Wasn't showing up as a problem in tests, but thought better safe than sorry.
